agnetic field and bias\nbut mostly for Landau level $M=0.$ The applicability of the 2BM in trilayer\ngraphene, even for level $M=0,$ is much more restricted. In this case, the 2BM\\\nfails to reproduce some of the level crossings that occur between the\nsub-levels of $M=0.$\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 28 Oct 2013 19:46:12 GMT"}],"update_date":"2014-01-08"}
